10. Ne5
{ Freeing the f3-square for the queen, and also kind of preventing Black to develop their knight to its most natural square, c6. }
10... b5 11. Qf3
{ Attacking the a8-rook with tempo and also stopping ...Bb7 for the moment. }
11... Ra7 12. Bb3
{ We have a very nice initiative here. The rook on a7 is misplaced, and also it is not easy for our opponent to finish the development. For example, the most natural move leads to a very bad position for Black. }
