{ Eyeing the a7-rook. Black can and should try to blockade White's d5 ideas. }
13... Nd5
{ The most natural and the worst way :@@EndBracket@@ to do it, but  13...Ra8  14.Nxf7!  is already crushing:  14...Rxf7  15.Qxe6  Qe8  16.Qxf7  Qxf7  17.Rxe7+-  .   @@StartFEN@@1n1q1rk1/rb2bppp/p3pn2/1p2N3/3P4/1BN1Q3/PP3PPP/R1B1R1K1 b - - 5 13@@EndFEN@@  13...Bd5  is the best move, but after  14.Nxd5  exd5   @@StartBracket@@  14...Nxd5  is losing to  15.Nxf7!  with Qxe6 to follow@@EndBracket@@  15.Qf3  White has a clear advantage: Bg5 is coming, the d5-pawn is weak, and the knight is still on b8. }
14. Nxf7 { Counterattacking the opponent's queen. } 14... Nxe3
{ If instead  14...Rxf7  then  15.Qxe6  Bb4  16.Nxd5  and Black is once again losing the game on the a2-g8 diagonal.  16...Bxd5  17.Qxd5  Rad7  18.Qe4  Bxe1  19.Qxe1+-  with at least a clear pawn up for White. }
15. Nxd8 Nxg2 16. Rxe6 { And Black's position is completely lost. } *

