4. e3 e6 5. Bxc4 c5 6. O-O a6 7. dxc5
{ Black has to make a big decision here. If they take on d1, then they will bring our rook into the game with tempo but will keep the option to castle. Instead, in the case of ...Bxc5, they are not giving this tempo, but their king will remain in the centre. Of course, given it is an endgame, doesn't look like a big deal, but that king on e7 can get unpleasant checks from a3, and retreating the bishop to e7 will be also impossible.   It is hard to say which one is the better way:  7...Qxd1  is more popular overall, but recently there are more games with  7...Bxc5  on the highest level. }
