{ If instead  10...Nc6  , then after  11.a3  we just transposed to the 9...Nc6 line. }
11. Ne5 b5
{ This move is again somewhat dubious, because we can activate our rook by playing a4, and Black will have quite a few weak squares on the queenside. }
12. a4 bxa4 13. Rxa4 Bb7 14. Nb3 Rxd1+ 15. Bxd1
{ Our pieces are more active, and the a6-pawn is much more accessible than the b2-pawn. }
