11. Bh4 O-O 12. h3
{ Precisely! First making the bishop very passive, and only then taking the pawn. Instead,  12.Nxd5  would lead to huge complications after  12...Re8  , for example, but  12...g5  is also available for Black with decent counterchances. }
12... Bh5 13. g4 Bg6 14. f5
