10. O-O Nbd7
{ Up to this moment, we were following the 'Keep It Simple for Black' course. In this position, I recommend an interesting, basically unexplored concept. }
11. a4
{ This move looks very antipositional. It is not even the right way to start the minority attack, because Black can stop it very effectively with ...a5! in this case. The point of this move is that, before playing f3, we are stopping Black's main idea, to play ...b5! Without that move, they have a hard time creating counterplay against our central play. }
11... a5 12. f3 { We return to our normal plan. } 12... b6 13. Kh1
{ With Bf2 and e4 coming as usual, but Black doesn’t have their standard counterplay with ...b5. }
