11... Be7 12. Ne2 { The other knight is coming to f5 too! } 12... Nb6
{ This move looks better than  12...f5  , but probably Black is just not in time. }
13. Ng3 Bb4+ 14. Kd1 Na4 15. Ngf5
{ So far we were following the game Carlsen-Kramnik @@StartBracket@@see the full gamehere@@EndBracket@@ and the current World Champion managed to occupy the f5-square with the knight and later converted this endgame.   It is important that Black can't take on b2:  15...Nxb2+?!  16.Kc2  Nc4  17.Bxc4  dxc4  18.Rhb1  and we are winning the pawn back with a better position. }
