{ Finally, we can make this move since we are ready to face ...h6 thanks to an important tactical idea! }
10... Nf8 11. f3
{ Preparing e4, but we have to be careful. One of the basic ideas to check when we are ready to push the pawn is what happens after dxe4-fxe4, Ng4! }
11... Be6
{ Finishing development and preparing to play ...Rc8. Instead,  11...Ne6??  would be a huge mistake, since Black just loses a pawn after  12.Bxf6!  Bxf6  13.Bxh7+-  Black could start with  11...b5  as well. The most useful move for us, in that case, is  12.Kh1  and eventually Black will have to play  12...h6  or  12...g6  in order to bring the f8-knight to the game, so eventually it will be just a transposition tothe 11...h6 line orthe 11...g6 line respectively. }
12. Rad1 Rc8 13. Ng3 Ng6 14. a3
{ Just a useful waiting move. It is not easy to improve the position for Black. }
14... c5
{ 14...a5  15.Kh1⩲  and we are keeping both e4 and f4 ideas in the air. } 15.
dxc5 Bxc5 16. Kh1
{ Stepping out from the diagonal. The pin on the h4-d8 diagonal is unpleasant, and we also have the active idea of pushing f4-f5. }
