11... Nh5
{ This move gives up on the ...Ng4 idea, making e4 easier to achieve.  11...N6d7?  has the same problem: there is no ...Ng4 anymore, so e4 is coming very quickly.  12.Bxe7  Qxe7  13.e4  dxe4  14.fxe4±  With a clear advantage for White because of the nice centre. }
12. Bxe7 Rxe7
{ Keeping the queen on d8, and therefore keeping an eye on the d4 pawn as well.   Instead, if  12...Qxe7  , then we can simply play  13.e4  dxe4  14.fxe4±  and have a clear advantage. }
13. Qd2
{ We don't have to rush!  13.e4  would play into Black's hands, since after  13...dxe4  14.fxe4  Ne6  there is pressure on our centre or more precisely on our d4-pawn. }
13... Ne6 14. Rad1 { With Bb1 and finally e4 to follow. } *

