Nf3 Ng6 10. Bh2 { The point of h2-h3. } 10... Bd6 11. Bxd6 Qxd6 12. Qc2
{ With standard play for both sides: Black will try to create some counterplay on the kingside and White will turn to the queenside. }
12... O-O 13. O-O Re8 14. Rab1
{ And we just transposed to the variation which starts with7...O-O instead of 7...Nbd7. }
