10. O-O d4 11. exd4 Nxd4
{ Most of the games have ended in a draw from this position, but I believe with precise moves we can still put pressure on our opponent. }
12. Na4 Nxe2+ 13. Bxe2
{ The light-squared bishop is getting closer to its optimal diagonal. } 13...
Nd5
{ Counterattacking on f4 is the main move in this position. If  13...Be7  14.Bf3  Qa5  15.Nc3  White's bishops exert an annoying pressure on the queenside, whereas Black hasn't solved the development of the c8-bishop yet.   13...Bd4  is simply met by  14.Bf3  and it is hard to point Black's next move. }
14. Be5 Be7 15. Qd4 { Centralisation! } 15... Bf6 16. Bf3
{ And of course, I don't doubt that engines can hold such a position, but it is definitely not pleasant for a human. }
