4. cxd5 exd5
{ Regarding the development of the c8-bishop, ...c6 is the most useful 3rd move that Black can play against us. It protects the d5-pawn, and also very often, when the bishop comes to f5, we could counter it by playing Qb3. Here, ...c6 opens the possibility for Black to simply block it with ...Qb6 without weakening the pawn structure on the queenside. }
5. Bf4
{ The best we can do is to continue the development! The only option to stop ...Bf5 is to play  5.Qc2  , but here Black plays  5...Bd6!  and we are struggling with our c1-bishop! }
