{ Instead,  9...b5  is a tricky but very bad move.  10.Bxb5!  Qa5+  and it looks like that Black is winning a piece but after  11.Nc3!+-  they actually have to resign because our bishop is protected, Black's knight is hanging on c6 with a check and the d4-pawn is also hanging. }
10. Bd2 Bxd2+
{ Maybe the trickiest choice from Black, since it looks like we have to recapture with the knight, where actually Black is okay! Instead,  10...dxe3  11.Bxb4  Qxd1+  12.Rxd1  Rxa4  13.Bc3  is just winning for White, because both Bb5 and Bg7 are threatened.  10...d3  is also pretty easy to handle:  11.Bxb4  Nxb4  12.Nd4!  stopping ...Nc2 and preparing for a3 to collect the pawn on d3. }
11. Qxd2 { Important to remember this tactical idea! } 11... Rxa4 12. Bb5
{ We are taking back the piece with interest! } *

