7... Bxc5
{ By far the best move in the position is to take back the pawn immediately. Instead,  7...Nf6  is not addressing our next move  8.e3  at all and after  8...Bg4  9.Be2  Black is already in trouble:  9...b5  is just losing to the nice  10.Nxd4!  , while after  @@StartFEN@@r2qkb1r/pp3ppp/2n2n2/2P5/N2p2b1/4PN2/PP2BPPP/R1BQK2R b KQkq - 2 9@@EndFEN@@  9...Bxc5  10.O-O  Be7  11.Nxd4  Bxe2  12.Nxe2±  we ended up with an extra pawn.   7...Bf5  is a little bit better than ...Nf6, but still very dubious.  8.e3  d3  was the idea behind ...Bf5, but after  9.a3!  stopping ...Nb4 ideas, it is hard to come up with anything active for Black. A possible line is  9...Nf6  10.b4  Qd5  11.Nc3±  with the idea of pushing b5 and then Nd4 and collect the pawn on d3. }
