[Event "?"]
[Site "?"]
[Date "????.??.??"]
[Round "?"]
[White "12) Austrian / Symmetrical Defence"]
[Black "Austrian Defence: 3...Nf6 #1"]
[Result "*"]

1. d4 d5 2. c4 c5
{ This is the so-called Austrian or Symmetrical Defence. Black immediately wants to solve their opening problems by copying White and exchanging all the pawns in the centre. The main downside of Black's play is how to finish development or not to get too far behind, since their queen coming immediately into play offers White chances to gain some tempi. }
3. cxd5
{ The most logical move, inviting the black queen into the game to speed our development at its expense. }
3... Nf6
{ Black rather develops first, planning to take back the pawn on d5 with the knight. In case we take on c5, our opponent has ...Qa5+ ideas. }
4. e4
{ An important move to remember! Instead of the queen, now it's the knight's turn to go on an early journey and make a few moves in a row. That will give us a lead in development. }
4... Nxe4 { A must. Otherwise, Black is just down a pawn. } 5. dxc5
{ We continue asking questions: how does Black want to regain the missing pawn? }
5... Qa5+
{ This move has the same downside we'll see inthe 3...Qxd5 lines: we can use threats against the queen to speed up our development. }
6. Bd2 Nxd2 { Instead,  6...Qxc5??  is just losing a piece after  7.Qa4+  . }
7. Qxd2 Qxc5
{ Black has managed to take back the pawn and their structure is even better, since we have an isolated pawn on d5, so long-term Black's position is even preferable. This means we have to play energetically and forcefully, and we will! }
8. Na3 { Rc1 is a huge threat, winning the bishop on c8! } 8... Bd7 9. Rc1
{ The first tempo on the queen! } 9... Qb6 10. Nc4 { And the second one! }
10... Qf6 11. Nf3
{ White is clearly better here. Black is seriously behind in development, and after we play Nce5, their only developed piece, the d7-bishop, has to move again if the knight wants to leave b8. Note what I said about the d5-pawn: though a potential issue for the endgames, now it is a very strong pawn, which gives us a space advantage in the centre. }
*

[Event "?"]
[Site "?"]
