[Black "Austrian Defence: 3...cxd4"]
[Result "*"]

1. d4 d5 2. c4 c5
{ This is the so-called Austrian or Symmetrical Defence. Black immediately wants to solve their opening problems by copying White and exchanging all the pawns in the centre. The main downside of Black's play is how to finish development or not to get too far behind, since their queen coming immediately into play offers White chances to gain some tempi. }
3. cxd5
{ The most logical move, inviting the black queen into the game to speed our development at its expense. }
3... cxd4
{ As in 99.9% of cases in chess, eventually Black has to stop playing the copying game. Otherwise, they will have big problems. Here this moment comes pretty early. }
4. Qxd4 Nf6
{ I guess it doesn't require a deep analysis why  4...Qxd5  is not really advisable. :@@EndBracket@@ }
5. Nc3 { White can easily keep their extra pawn. } 5... e6 6. e4 exd5 7. exd5
{ Black has absolutely no compensation for the pawn. We'll finish development and play with a very strong extra pawn. }
