{ The Marshall Defence, a dubious opening where Black is not supporting the pawn on d5 with another pawn. Instead, the knight goes to d5, somewhat similarly to the Grünfeld Defence. As we will see, there is a major difference which will give White a clear advantage. }
3. cxd5
{ Of course, this is the best reply. We are not waiting for Black to correct their mistake and play 3...c6 or 3...e6 in the next move. }
3... Nxd5
{ No gambits. The other recapture,  3...Qxd5  , would be very bad. White can just play  4.Nc3  developing with tempo, and the queen has to look for a new square immediately. }
