7... exd5 8. e5 d4 9. Bc4 Ng4
{ Relatively the best move. Instead,  9...Be6?  is just losing because of  10.Bxe6  fxe6  11.exf6  and here Black can't take our knight because f7+ would win the queen. Therefore, Black tried  11...Qa5  in a couple of games, but after let's say  12.Qe2+-  the game is just over.   9...dxc3  is not much better:  10.Bxf7+  Ke7  11.exf6  gxf6  12.Bd5  also leads to a winning position for White. }
10. Qb3 Qd7
{ Obviously, Black can't allow Bxf7+ or go for  10...Qc7  11.Nd5+-  or  @@StartFEN@@rnbqkb1r/pp3ppp/8/2p1P3/2Bp2n1/1QN2N2/PP3PPP/R1B1K2R b KQkq - 3 10@@EndFEN@@  10...Qe7  11.Nd5+-  and White wins in all cases. }
11. O-O
{ White has a huge attack against the king in the centre. For instance,  11...dxc3  12.Rd1  cxb2  13.Bxb2  Qe7  14.e6  fxe6  15.Re1  is one sample line of how the game could very quickly end in White's favour. }
