12... Nxd4
{ Black decides to liquidate material. Otherwise, Bb5 with pressure on the queenside would be annoying. }
13. Qxd4 Qxd4 14. Bxd4 f6
{ Black needs to defend g7 and  14...Nf5  15.Bc3  is temporary, as the knight will have to move soon. }
15. Be2
{ A typical endgame position for this opening variation. White is better, having the bishop pair and a more mobile pawn majority. }
