[White "16) Albin Countergambit"]
[Black "Albin Countergambit: Black's trick"]
[Result "*"]

1. d4 d5 2. c4 e5
{ This is the Albin Countergambit, a pretty risky opening with a dubious reputation. The only player who is using it relatively frequently on the top is Alexander Morozevich, though mainly in rapid or blitz games. }
3. dxe5 d4 { Let me show you the basic trick of this opening variation. } 4. e3
{ This looks like the most logical move in the position, immediately undermining Black's main asset, the strong d4-pawn. However, this is exactly what Black players are hoping for. }
4... Bb4+ 5. Bd2 dxe3
{ This is the key move. Now White should recapture on e3 and play with a pretty bad structure, but Black is already fine there. }
6. Bxb4
{ Happened in 75 OTB games according to my database, not to mention about thousands of online games. White is already losing here! }
6... exf2+ 7. Ke2 { The king has to protect the queen on d1. } 7... fxg1=N+
{ Promoting to knight at move 7@@StartBracket@@!@@EndBracket@@ with a check decides the game. Once the rook recaptures, ...Bg4+ will pick up the d1-queen. }
