6... O-O 7. a3 { Asking the bishop to make a decision: take on c3 or go back. }
7... Bxc3+ 8. Qxc3
{ Black is giving up the pair of bishops, but in return they want to have a strong knight on e4. }
8... a5
{ If Black goes for the positional approach, with the threat of ...a4, we don't really have to react: without the knight on e4, Black will not have active pieces. }
9. Bd3 a4 10. Qc2
{ The knight is not coming to e4 anymore, and Black can also have problems with the a4-pawn later. }
10... Bd7 11. Bd2
{ In case of ...Na5 we can always reply with Ne5. Otherwise, we can just castle and then play Rac1, Rfd1 and see what Black is going to do with their awkward minor pieces. }
