1. d4 Nf6 2. c4 e6 3. Nc3 Bb4
{ The Nimzo-Indian Defence, a popular opening at all levels. Maybe in this opening, as in the Ruy Lopez against 1.e4, it is easier to say who hasn't played it than who has.Black's idea with 3...Bb4 is very simple: stopping the e4 move and also developing a piece in the process. }
4. Qb3
{ This is the 9th@@StartBracket@@!@@EndBracket@@ most popular move in the position, and called the Spielmann Variation. It fits well with our repertoire: it doesn't allow doubled pawns on c3, it avoids the sharpest lines which require a lot of memorisation, and also asks Black a question about their bishop on b4. There is only one good way to answer it. }
4... Nc6
{ Protecting the bishop on b4 and attacking d4 at the same time, since after ...Nxd4, Qxb4 is not an option: we lose the queen to ...Nc2+. }
5. e3
{ Maybe the most important move to remember of the whole 4...Nc6 variation!  5.Nf3  would be inaccurate because of  5...Ne4!  and Black will take on c3 with the bishop doubling our pawns, and then support their knight with ...f5.By playing e3, we keep the option to kick out the knight from e4 with f3. }
5... O-O 6. a3 Bxc3+
{ Black can insist on keeping the bishop with  6...Ba5  , but after  7.Qc2  @@StartBracket@@with the threat of b4@@EndBracket@@ they will have to eventually take on c3. }
7. Qxc3 d6 { Going for the e5-plan straight away. } 8. Bd3 e5 9. Ne2 Re8
{ Nothing unusual so far, but here we have to be careful. } 10. O-O
{ Instead,  10.d5  looks pretty tempting, but Black has  10...e4!  11.Bc2  Ne5  12.Ng3  c6!  with counterplay. For example,  13.dxc6  bxc6  14.b3  d5  with mutual chances. }
10... d5
{ Black has to play actively in the centre. Otherwise, they are just clearly worse. The only OTB game which reached this position went  10...e4?  and after  11.Bc2  d5  12.f3!  with Ng3 or Nf4 to follow, Black is in great difficulties because their centre is falling apart. }
11. dxe5 Nxe5 12. cxd5 Nxd3 13. Qxd3 Qxd5 14. Qc3
{ With f3 and e4 coming, Black is still slightly worse, but their position is definitely playable. }
