{ The most natural move, but it leaves the f5-square undefended. Black could step out of the pin with  14...Qe6  ready to meet  15.Ng3  with  15...g5!  , so White should go  @@StartFEN@@r1b2rk1/2pn1pp1/1p2qn1p/p3p3/2P4B/P1QBP3/1P2NPPP/3R1RK1 w - - 0 15@@EndFEN@@  15.f4!  Using the development lead, White is forcing concrete play.  15...exf4  16.Nd4  Qxe3+  17.Kh1  Ne4  18.Qc2  Ndc5  19.Be2±  White has the threat of Rf3 and Black is in bad shape, according to the computer. }
