{ Defending and counterattacking! If instead  12...O-O  , then we can play  13.Nxe5!  @@StartBracket@@the d4-pawn is hanging now@@EndBracket@@  13...Nc3  14.Bc4  Be6  15.O-O  and we finished the development and have a healthy extra pawn. }
13. Bb5+ Bd7 14. Bxd7+ Qxd7 15. O-O
{ We finished the development with a huge advantage, as Black's position is pretty loose. Two moves have been tried here OTB.  15...dxe3  16.Bxe3  and here according to the engine it is the best to castle and give up the pawn on e5 for free, since everything else is much worse. For example:  16...f6  17.Rad1  Qc6  18.Qb3  and Black is completely lost, even unable to castle.  15...O-O-O  is a somewhat better try:  16.exd4  exd4  17.h3  h5   @@StartBracket@@if  17...Ngf6  , then we can use our f1-rook:  18.Rd1  d3  19.Be3  and besides the d3-pawn, Black's king is also very weak@@EndBracket@@  18.b5!  with ideas like c6 or b6, and Black's king is much weaker than its colleague. }
