1. d4 Nf6 2. c4 c5 3. d5 b5
{ This is the starting position of the Benkő Gambit. Alternatively,  3...a6  is a tricky move. Black wants to tempt us into some  4.Nc3  b5  Benkő.   In case of  4.Qc2  they can even go for the Benoni with ...e6 and then we don't want our queen on c2.   The best approach is to play  4.a4  and stop ...b5 completely, and the game will most likely transpose into some kind of Benoni, depending on Black's next move. }
4. Qc2
{ We don't give Black the possibility to have the initiative after 10 moves or so. Therefore, we decline the gambit, and at the same time we get ready to push e4 and occupy the centre! }
4... Qa5+ { This check doesn't really disrupt our development. } 5. Nd2
{ In many cases the knight is even happy to go to d2 since the main goal is to reach the c4-square. }
5... bxc4 6. e4 d6 7. Bxc4 g6 8. b3
{ One of the reasons why 4...Qa5+ is not causing us a big headache is that, although the bishop usually goes to the long diagonal via d2, playing b3+Bb2 is also perfectly fine. }
8... Nxe4
{ This would be a brilliant tactical trick if not for White's strong reply. }
9. b4 { Black's nice idea was  9.Qxe4  Bf5  10.Qe3  Bg7∞  trapping the rook. }
9... Qxb4
{ 9...cxb4  10.Nxe4  b3+  11.Qc3+-  is an extra piece, and White also wins on the spot after  @@StartFEN@@rnb1kb1r/p3pp1p/3p2p1/q2P4/1pB1N3/8/P1Q2PPP/R1B1K1NR b KQkq - 0 10@@EndFEN@@  10...Bg7  11.Bb3!+-  closing the a5-e1 diagonal and attacking c8. }
10. Qxe4 Bf5
{ If instead  10...Qc3  11.Bb5+!  Bd7  12.Bxd7+  Nxd7  13.Rb1+-  White has an extra piece and Bb2 comes next.  @@StartFEN@@rnb1kb1r/p3pp1p/3p2p1/1BpP4/4Q3/2q5/P2N1PPP/R1B1K1NR b KQkq - 0 11@@EndFEN@@  11...Kd8  12.Qa4!  Qxa1  13.Qa5#  or  @@StartFEN@@rnbk1b1r/p3pp1p/3p2p1/1BpP4/Q7/2q5/P2N1PPP/R1B1K1NR b KQ - 0 12@@EndFEN@@  12...Bf5  13.Ne2  Qxa1  14.O-O+-  and we are down an exchange, but it is okay if we deliver checkmate :@@EndBracket@@ }
11. Qe3 Bg7 12. a3 { The point of tempting the queen to take on b4! } 12... Qb7
13. Ra2
{ And White keeps the extra piece thanks to the tempo gained by a3, vacating this square for the rook. }
