[Result "*"]

1. d4 Nf6 2. c4 c5 3. d5 b5
{ This is the starting position of the Benkő Gambit. Alternatively,  3...a6  is a tricky move. Black wants to tempt us into some  4.Nc3  b5  Benkő.   In case of  4.Qc2  they can even go for the Benoni with ...e6 and then we don't want our queen on c2.   The best approach is to play  4.a4  and stop ...b5 completely, and the game will most likely transpose into some kind of Benoni, depending on Black's next move. }
4. Qc2
{ We don't give Black the possibility to have the initiative after 10 moves or so. Therefore, we decline the gambit, and at the same time we get ready to push e4 and occupy the centre! }
4... bxc4 5. e4
{ Of course, we want to take back on c4 with the bishop and not with the queen. }
5... e6 6. Nc3 exd5 7. e5
{ The sharpest and most tactical line of the whole 4.Qc2 variation. } 7... Bb7
{ The best move, giving up a piece but keeping interesting counterchances with a flexible centre. }
8. exf6 Qxf6 9. Nf3 Be7
{ Alternatively, Black can play  9...Na6  10.Bg5  Nb4  11.Qd2  Qf5  12.Qe3+  Qe6  13.O-O-O±  . The position is full of tension, but it's Black who has to make concessions first in order to finish development. For instance, after  13...f6  14.Bf4  d4  15.Qxe6+  dxe6  16.Nb5  e5  17.Bg3  White has managed to create targets for the minor pieces, which is the key for this position, and therefore keeps a clear advantage. }
10. Bg5 Qe6+ 11. Be2 d4 12. O-O dxc3
{ This position is very rich, with many interesting possibilities for White. I'll offer one way to reach a slightly better endgame. }
13. Rae1 { We have threats like Bxc4 on the board now. } 13... Nc6 14. Qxc3 O-O
15. Bxc4 Qd6 16. Bxe7 Nxe7
{ Black is defending well, so the maximum I could achieve here was a slightly better endgame. }
17. Ne5 Bc6 18. Qd3
{ This move is a little bit surprising. White has other moves as well, but here we just take back the pawn, and play an endgame with a better structure. }
18... Qxd3 19. Nxd3 Ng6 20. Nxc5
{ The queenside majority and the weak d-pawn offer White better chances. } *

