7. cxd5
{ Despite all the scary threats we can just take the second pawn! It simply works! }
7... Ne4 { This is much less challenging than  7...Nxd5  . } 8. Be5
{ We can neutralise the pressure on the long diagonal very nicely with the help of this move. }
8... Nxc3 { Instead,  8...Bxe5  9.Nxe5  Nxc3  10.Qd2  is the same trick! } 9.
Qd2 { And we have a completely winning position with a healthy extra pawn. }
9... Bxe5 10. Nxe5 Qxc5 11. Rc1
{ White keeps the extra pawn with a huge advantage. } *

