9... Be6 { Much trickier than  9...Bxd2+  . } 10. Qxb7
{ Instead,  10.Bxc3  Qxc3+  11.bxc3  Bxd5  is at least equal, but rather slightly better for Black because our c-pawns are very weak in that endgame. }
10... Bxd2+ 11. Nxd2 O-O 12. b4
{ Instead,  12.Qxa8  is only enough for a draw:  12...Rd8!  and Black is threatening not only ...Qxd2 but also ...Bd5! to trap the queen. The only move for White is  13.b4!  Qxb4  14.Rd1  , and since now ...Bd5 is not possible because the a7-pawn is hanging, Black has to go for the perpetual with  14...Rxd2  15.Rxd2  Qb1+  16.Rd1  Qb4  with a draw. }
