{ Continuing the development. Of course, the other moves we want to play later, such as  5.Rc1  or  5.e3  , are also possible. Since this opening is very concrete, or move by move, those moves would offer Black some extra options, or lead to different positions altogether. }
5... O-O 6. Rc1 dxc4
{ Black is allowing us to occupy the centre, and they will build their counterplay on playing ...Bg4 and putting pressure on the centre. }
7. e4 Bg4
{ Black is pinning our knight and ready to play ...Nh5 as well, to open the diagonal for their g7-bishop and put more pressure on our centre. }
8. Bxc4 Nh5
{ 8...Bxf3  is also possible, but after  9.gxf3  Nh5  10.Be3  we just transpose back to our main line. }
9. Be3 Bxf3 10. gxf3
{ We have to keep the d4-pawn protected. Black has to act quickly here: if we can stabilise our position, then we are just clearly better with the strong centre and pair of bishops. In some games  10.Qxf3  was tried, but after  10...Bxd4  11.O-O  c5!  we can speak about compensation for the pawn at most, but definitely no advantage for White. }
10... e5
{ The main move. Black is challenging our central dominance. Even though it will most likely lead to an endgame, Black is hoping the control over the f4-square will offer enough compensation for White's pair of bishops. }
11. dxe5 Bxe5 12. Qxd8 Rxd8 13. O-O
{ Our goal in this endgame is to play f4. If we can do that, then we are clearly better with the 2 bishops. If not, then Black is probably fine. }
13... Nc6 14. Nd5
{ Already threatening f4! The b2-pawn is not really hanging, since Rb1-Rxb7 is not something which Black would like to see. }
14... Na5 15. Be2 { Keeping the pair of bishops! } 15... c6
{ Black is kicking back our knight with tempo, but at the same time they are putting their knight on a5 into a very bad situation. }
16. Nc3 { We are actually threatening to trap it with b4! } 16... b5 17. b3
{ Not allowing ...Nc4! } 17... Nf4 18. Rfe1 Nb7 19. Bf1
{ With Rc2 @@StartBracket@@stepping out of ...Nd3@@EndBracket@@ and then Ne2, we have good chances to eventually push f4, and in the meantime Black also created a weakness on c6. }
