19. Bd3 Qf6
{ For a second the queen is unprotected here, so we can use this tempo to activate our knight. }
20. Nf5 Nd7 21. Ng3
{ The e4-square will be a nice one for the knight: it will attack the d6-pawn, block the counterplay on the e-file, and in some cases can jump to g5 to create some threats. }
21... Qd4 22. Bb1 Re7
{ 22...Nf6?  This way Black can stop the knight from reaching e4, but it also has some issues:  23.Bxg6!  fxg6  24.Qxg6  Kf8  25.Nf5+-  attacking the queen and threatening mate. }
23. Rf1 Rae8 24. Ne4
{ Black has to take care of the d6-pawn and if that happens, we can start a new wave of the attack by pushing our h4 pawn. }
