{ The most logical move, winning some time, since White doesn't want the endgame. }
20. Qg5 Nd7
{ Instead, Black can't go on with offering the queen exchange again, because  20...Qe5  21.Nf5!  allows our knight into the game. With f4 coming, Black's position is just losing. }
21. f4
{ Controlling the e5-square and preparing the f3-square for the knight. After playing Nf3 we will have to attack on the kingside, which will happen by playing f5 or pushing h4-h5. The queen exchange is only an option for us if we win some material immediately after it.This position is balanced according to the computer, but in practical terms, I rather favour our immediate attacking chances on the kingside to a potentially better endgame for Black. }
