{ This is an interesting move which forces White to be precise. } 11. Rc1
{ If White is careless and plays  11.h3  with the idea of covering the g4-square and preparing Nf3, then  11...Qb4  can cause some issues. }
11... Nc6 12. h3
{ Covering the g4-square, so our important bishop on e3 is not exposed to a potential Ng4. }
12... Nd4 13. b3
{ Instead,  13.Nf3  would have been inaccurate because  13...Nxe2  14.Qxe2  Qb4!  and we have problems to defend the c4-pawn. }
13... Kh7 14. Bd3
{ We will play Nge2 next, get rid of the d4-knight, and Black's weak square on d5 and the backward pawn on d6 gives us the advantage. }
