7. Nf3 Ne7
{ 7...Nf6  8.Nd2  O-O  9.Nc4  Ne8  Black is ready to play ...f5.  10.h4!  Very strong! Our king is not yet committed to the kingside, and we can take full advantage of it.  10...f5  11.h5  Nd7  12.hxg6  Opening up lines in front of the black king.  12...hxg6  13.exf5  gxf5  14.Bh6±  Qd2 is coming and, without the dark-squared bishops, Black's king is going to face a serious attack. }
8. h4 { Pretty much forcing ...h5 and making ...f5 much less appealing. } 8...
h5 9. a5 Nd7 10. Bd2
{ Na4 followed by b4 is a strong plan to break Black's queenside. } 10... O-O
11. Na4
{ If Black were to wait here, b4 would come with a huge initiative for White. }
11... f5
{ Looking for some counterplay, but this will backfire and create more weaknesses. }
12. Ng5 Nf6 13. Nb6 Rb8 14. f3
{ The idea of b4 is still very unpleasant for Black, who also has to watch out for moves like Nxc8 and then a white knight landing on e6. }
