6... c6
{ That's what Black ideally wants to do: play c6, then d5, and build a very strong centre. }
7. Bg2 d5 8. f3
{ The position resembles very much a reversed French Defence. As in the French with f6, here f3 is coming with great power and Black's centre is falling apart. }
8... exf3 { 8...e3?  9.Nf1+-  and we are taking on e3 in the next move. } 9.
Nxf3 dxc4 10. e4
{ We have a wonderful centre and a big advantage in the development. Black is in serious trouble. If they try  10...Nxe4?  , then after  11.O-O!  their position is almost losing. }
