{ Getting rid of the c6-pawn, thus further weakening the diagonal. } 9... cxd5
10. f3
{ And then the well-known breakthrough from the French gives us a huge advantage. }
10... Nc6 11. fxe4 dxe4 { 11...Nxd4??  loses a piece to  12.Qa4+  . } 12. e3
{ Our centre is very strong, while Black's pawn on e4 will fall very soon. } *

