Re8 12. Be2
{ Putting a piece in front of our king makes f4 possible again. That is kind of an important move, since Black's neutralising idea against the pressure on the long diagonal is to play ...Be5 at some point. }
12... b6 13. Rg1 Bb7 14. f4
{ With Nd5 and Qd4 to follow. White has a very strong attack, and our king is perfectly safe in the centre. }
