8... Nc6 { 8...O-O  9.Ne2  Nc6  just transposes to  8...Nc6  . } 9. Ne2 b5
{ Black is stopping c4, but this pawn can't stay on b5 for too long. } 10. a4
{ Since Black can protect the pawn with neither ...Rb8 nor with ...Qb6, it has to go forward. }
10... b4 11. c4 { The first c4! } 11... bxc3 12. bxc3
{ We are threatening c4 again. } 12... Na5 13. Ned4
{ With Nb3 to follow, exchanging the knight on a5 and then pushing c4 for the second time. }
