{ Instead,  6...e6  just gives us additional options. We can just play our normal setup with  7.Nf3  , but  7.Bxa6  is also very interesting @@StartBracket@@this would be my choice@@EndBracket@@ to make the black structure really ugly. For instance  7...bxa6  8.Nf3  c5  9.O-O  Be7  10.Na4  offers White some clear positional advantage. Black's position is full of weak squares and pawns. }
