[Result "*"]

1. d4 f5
{ The Dutch Defence, a very interesting, fighting opening. Black is immediately breaking the symmetry, and depending on our reply  2.Nf3  or  2.g3  , they can go for the Leningrad @@StartBracket@@playing ...Nf6 and ...g6@@EndBracket@@ or for the Classical Dutch  @@StartBracket@@playing ...Nf6 and ...e6@@EndBracket@@. }
2. Nc3
{ With this move we are announcing that we want to play neither the Leningrad nor the Classical Dutch. Compared to the main lines which start with  2.g3  or  2.Nf3  and lead to complex, strategical battles, our move is much more direct and aggressive, we want to play e4 on the next move, and highlight the fact that with ...f5 being played, Black's king is a little bit open. }
2... g6
{ This move is not addressing our e4-idea, and also creates a hook for our h-pawn. }
3. h4 { Black is already clearly worse here! } 3... Nf6
{ If instead  3...Bg7  , then for example  4.h5  d6  5.e4  and Black is in a very tough situation. White is attacking in the centre and on the kingside. }
4. h5 Nxh5 5. Rxh5
{ If you don't feel like sacrificing an exchange,  5.e4  also gives a big advantage according to the engine but, in my opinion, this Rxh5 move is not really a sacrifice. Black's king will be simply too weak. }
5... gxh5 6. e4 { With a mate-in-1 idea! } 6... Bg7
{ 6...d6  and trying to run with the king towards the queenside is not much better:  7.Bc4  c6  8.Nh3  fxe4  9.Qxh5+  Kd7  10.Ng5+-  is one possible line, with Nf7 or Ne6 to follow. Black is in very bad shape. }
7. Qxh5+ Kf8 8. Qxf5+ Kg8 9. Nf3
{ We have a knight and a pawn for the rook @@StartBracket@@which is not really active on h8...@@EndBracket@@ and according to the engine our advantage is +3, which shouldn't come as a big surprise even by just looking at Black's position. }
