[Result "*"]

1. d4 e6 2. c4 b6
{ The starting position of the English Defence, which will have very little independent value regarding our repertoire. }
3. a3 Bb7 4. Nc3 f5 5. Bf4 g5
{ A way to avoid the Classical Dutch after ...Nf6, but it is extremely risky.   5...Nf6  6.e3  is transposing tothe Classical Dutch chapter. }
6. Bd2 Qf6 7. h4 { Targeting the weak pawn on g5. } 7... g4 8. Nb5
{ Protecting d4 and attacking c7 at the same time. } 8... Na6 9. Bf4
{ The bishop returns to f4, so we can already consider 5...g5 as a failure. }
9... d6 10. Qa4 Kf7 11. O-O-O
{ White's king is much safer and our next moves are e3-Ne2, continuing development. }
