2. e4 Nf6 3. Nc3 g6
{ The starting position of the Pirc Defence. Since this is a 1.d4 repertoire, obviously I'm not going to recommend any of the main lines. Instead, my choice is like the 10th most common move in this position, but still perfectly compatible with our repertoire. }
4. h4 { We do this often, so why not here as well? } 4... Bg7
{ Black can calmly continue with this move, as h5 was not a threat yet because of the knight on f6. Instead,  4...h5  5.Nf3  Bg7  6.Ng5  is discussed viathe 2...g6 3.h4 h5 4.Nf3 Bg7 5.Nc3 Nf6 6.Ng5 move order. }
5. Be2 { Preparing for h5! } 5... c5
{ Black is counterattacking in the centre! } 6. dxc5
{ We take, since we really want to play h5 and that push will be possible once Black recaptures this pawn. }
6... Qa5
{ This is the point of 5...c5. Black threatens both ...Qxc5 and ...Nxe4. Instead,  6...dxc5?  is a serious mistake: White has a large advantage after  7.Qxd8+  Kxd8  8.Be3±  , with O-O-O and h5 to follow. }
