{ There are a couple of ways here to achieve a big advantage. I didn't choose the shortest way, but the most forcing one. }
12. dxc6 bxc6 13. Re1 Qxe2
{ Black was forced to take, as they would otherwise lose the queen to the pin. }
14. Rxe2+ Kd8 15. Na4
{ This move is the key to remember. Our next moves are checks and captures, ending in a winning position for White. }
15... Nxh1 16. Nxc5 Nxc5 17. Ba5+ Kd7 18. Ne5+ Ke8 19. Ng6+
{ Taking back the rook and keeping the extra pawn. } 19... Be6 20. Nxh8
{ Black's king doesn't really have a good square, while we have the clear g3-Bg2 idea to pick up the knight in the corner. }
*

