{ 8...c5?  is basically losing:  9.Qa4  d4  10.e5!  The cleanest!  dxc3  11.Bxc3  We sacrificed a piece but we have such a huge development lead that, according to the engine, we are already in +5, so resignable territory.  11...Ng4  12.Bc4+-  With a variety of winning threats. }
9. Qd3 O-O 10. exd5 Qc7
{ This is the main move, but it's hard to see enough compensation for the pawn. }
11. Ng5 { The knight can't leave f6, and we have the Nge4 idea. } 11... Bd6 12.
dxc6 bxc6 13. Qf3
{ Regrouping. The queen was oddly placed on d3, and now it has opened the way for the bishop to c4. }
13... Rb8 14. Nge4 { Black doesn't have enough compensation for the pawn. } *

