[White "40) Mexican Defence"]
[Black "Mexican Defence: 3...d5?"]
[Result "*"]

1. d4 Nf6 2. c4 Nc6
{ The Mexican Defence. Black wants to play ...e5, forcing us to play d5, then manoeuvre the knight to e7-g6, and have the g1-a7 diagonal for their bishop thanks to the control over the c5-square. }
3. Nf3 { The most popular response from White, stopping Black's ...e5 idea. }
3... d5
{ This move is very bad: Black's pieces will be kicked out of the centre. } 4.
cxd5 Qxd5
{ Instead,  4...Nxd5  5.e4!  is covered in theMarshall Defence chapter. } 5.
Nc3 Qa5 6. Bd2
{ I decided to put this line as a trainable variation because the very tempting  6.d5  is not so good, since after  6...Nb4  Black has some counterplay. }
6... Qf5 7. Rc1 { Black has very bad piece coordination. } *

