3... d6
{ Black insists on playing ...e5, but it is not the same as in the previous move, since the d6-pawn blocks the diagonal of the f8-bishop and it can't come to its ideal c5-square. }
4. Nc3
{ 4.d5  is a move I don't like so much because we would only help Black to solve the issue of the f8-bishop.  4...Ne5  5.Nxe5  dxe5  6.Nc3  e6!  and Black's position is perfectly playable, with the bishop coming to c5 or b4. }
4... e5
{ This is Black's main idea in this opening, but it's a passive setup. } 5. d5
{ We are forced to block the centre, but we have a nice space advantage. } 5...
Ne7 6. e4 Ng6
