7. h4 { Typical play against a knight on g6! } 7... Be7 8. h5 Nf8
{ 8...Nf4  looks more active, but the knight will be forced to a very bad square very soon.  9.h6!  g6  10.g3  N4h5  11.Be2±  The knight is horrible on h5 and we also have a strong pawn on h6. }
9. h6 g6 10. Be2 N8d7 11. Nh2
{ Preparing g4 and stopping Black's counterplay with ...f5 before they could even threaten us with it. }
11... O-O 12. g4
{ With Be3, Qc2/d2 and O-O-O coming. Eventually, we want to play on the queenside, as in the King's Indian Defence. }
