Bd7 18. Qb3 { White wouldn't mind playing an endgame against the IQP. } 18...
Qxb3
{ I believe it was better to try to keep the queens on the board. At least Black could then go for a little bit more complicated endgame than the one arising in the game.  18...Qc5  19.Qxb7  Rfb8  20.Nb3!  Otherwise, 19.Qxb7 would be just a serious inaccuracy.   20.Qa6  Rxb2⇆  Black has decent counterplay here. This is not something White is looking for.  20...Qxe3+  21.Rxe3  Rxb7  22.Rd1⩲  I prefer this endgame for Black to the one played in the game. It looks more difficult for White to put such a big pressure on the d5-pawn and, on a good day, Black may try playing with a5-a4.   @@StartFEN@@r4rk1/pp1b1pnp/5np1/2qp4/3N4/1QNBPP2/PP4PP/4RRK1 w - - 6 19@@EndFEN@@  19.Rf2  Bc6  20.Rc2  Qe7  21.Bf1⩲  Of course White is better and has the easier game, but at least Black has kept the queens on the board. }
